ecessity of teaching children about the facts of life is not questioned any more at least since the 18th century. And yet, there is disagreement regarding the contents and pedagogical realization of this process. Through sexual education books for children and families of the FRG (1050-2010) and their constructions of child sexuality, Christin Sager reconstructs the shift of societal normative structures and pedagogical debates on child sexuality and the practice of sexual education: Which constructions of family and gender, sexual norms, images of diversity, and discourses on sexualized violence manifest in the sexual education books?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aEducation. 0aSex instruction. 4aBRD. 4aBildung. 4aBildungsgeschichte. 4aFamiliensoziologie. 4aGender. 4aGeschichte der Kindheit. 4aGeschlechtergeschichte. 4aKinderladenbewegung. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aPädagogik. 4aSexualaufklärung. 4aSexualerziehung. 4aSexualität. 70(DE-588)4013134-80(DE-627)1046655480(DE-576)208901906aDruckwerk2gnd 70(DE-588)4030550-80(DE-627)1043601000(DE-576)208988165aKind2gnd 70(DE-588)4054684-60(DE-627)1047303740(DE-576)20911004XaSexualität2gnd 7aEDUCATION / History.2bisacsh  aCultural History.  aEducation.  aGender History.  aGender.  aHistory of Education.  aKinderladen Movement.  aPedagogy.  aSex Education.  aSexual Enlightment.  aSexuality.  aSociology of Family.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2015z9783110438741oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070099208iTitle i